com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.mem
Interface JNIEasyLibrary

All Superinterfaces:
DynamicLibrary
public interface JNIEasyLibrary
extends DynamicLibrary

The JNIEasyLibrary interface represents the framework's Dynamic Link Library (JNIEasy.dll).

Using this interface, DLL's exported native methods and fields are accessible to the Java world using internal framework classes and public using specific interfaces.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:

Method Detail

exportBehavior

boolean exportBehavior(java.lang.String nativeName,
                       NativeBehavior method)
Exports a native capable method instance with the specified name.

The instance is made first native (if already native does nothing) and registered in the DLL with the specified name. A native program (C or C++) can find this method using the JNIEasy.dll's exported method findExportedMethodAddress using as signature the returned String of the call:

method.getBehaviorSignature().getSignatureString(nativeName)

Parameters:
nativeName - the exported name of the method in the DLL, can be a macro based expression.
method - the native method instance to export.
Returns:
a native proxy instance of the DLL method.
See Also:
findExportedMethodAddress(String)

findExportedMethodAddress

NativeBehavior findExportedMethodAddress(java.lang.String signature)
Returns the native method instance registered with the specified signature.

The method is very similar to DynamicLibrary.findBehaviorBySignature(String), with two differences:

  1. The signature parameter admits an optional DLL name prefix:
    [DLLName:]signature
    DLLName is an optional DLL name, as used in DLLManager.get(String), to search the method, if missing the DLL to search is the framework´s DLL. signature is the method signature to search calling DynamicLibrary.findBehaviorBySignature(String) on the selected DLL.
  2. This method is the "Java view" of the JNIEasy.dll's exported method
    void* __stdcall findExportedMethodAddress(const char* signature);
    with the exported name "findExportedMethodAddress".

    The C version returns the address of the returned native method or NULL if no method is found.

Parameters:
signature - the signature string of the native method to search.
Returns:
the registered native method instance in the selected DLL or null if not found.

exportClassBehaviorsByDefault

java.util.Map exportClassBehaviorsByDefault(java.lang.Class cls,
                                            int callConv,
                                            boolean useReflection,
                                            boolean upperClasses,
                                            boolean skipNotValid)
Exports all methods and fields (as methods) of a class using the default native declarations.

It is a shortcut especially useful to export all methods and fields of a class (and optionally superclasses) using primitive or String types mainly.

Parameters:
cls - the class to export.
callConv - the call convention.
useReflection - if true BehaviorReflection objects are used, else NativeDirectCallback objects are used.
upperClasses - if true export the superclasses.
skipNotValid - if true avoids methods and fields with non-native capable types without throwing exceptions.
Returns:
the method/name indexed collection of native method instances exported.
See Also:
unexportClassBehaviorsByDefault(Class,boolean)

unexportClassBehaviorsByDefault

java.util.Map unexportClassBehaviorsByDefault(java.lang.Class cls,
                                              boolean upperClasses)
Un exports all methods and fields (as methods) of a class using the default native declarations.

It is the symmetric method of exportClassBehaviorsByDefault(Class,int,boolean,boolean,boolean).

Parameters:
cls - the class to export.
upperClasses - if true export the superclasses.
Returns:
the method/name indexed collection of native method instances removed.
